title: For Sale/Trade:  Nagant M1895 Revolver
postcontent: Looking to trade my 1944 M1895 Nagant Revolver, 7.62 x 38R.  This was my first revolver purchased as a fun novelty/historic item because this is one of the only revolvers that can be silenced.  The cylinder moves forward to the barrel before firing, and there are lots of videos online of this if you are interested. I only put 14 rounds through it, and noticed a problem.  When the gun is loaded and you are cocking it, it will sometimes lock up half way, and you will have to rotate the cylander by hand to fully cock it.  I looked online and saw this may be an indexing problem from someone swapping the cylanders refurbashing it, or it may simply not be "broken in" yet.  I do not know enough about the design or revolvers to tell you, but there is the full disclaimer.  I think the gun is a fun novelty item, but not something to ever depend on for defense. I paid $250 for it not knowing what was wrong, I am asking $200 or equivalent in trade.  Revolver comes with holster (leather strap for latch is torn), and box of 36 rounds by PPU.Will only sell to 21+, with VA ID, bill of sale, and CHP, or Voter Registration, or Active Military ID.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ithaca Model 900 12g Semi-Auto
postcontent: This is pretty rare Ithaca Model 900 made by SKB Japan. It is recoil operated much like the venerable Browning A-5. The production years for this model were 1968-1973. The gun looks good and is in nice condition for it's age. The internals are in great shape and honestly don't appear to show much use, and have been freshly cleaned and lubricated. This model uses a friction ring under the forearm to retard the speed of the action. For light loads, the friction cone can be turned flat side to the friction ring. For heavy loads, the friction cone can be flipped to further compress the friction ring during cycling. It is a simple yet brilliant design (Thanks John Browning!!!). The chamber is 2-3/4". The barrel length is 26" with a fixed Improved Cylinder choke. This would be a great bird gun and would be equally at home shooting trap or skeet. I'm asking $450 CASH or I'm really looking to trade for a nice Remington .243 ?? I WILL NOT SHIP!! Face to Face ONLY!!
